  "displayName": "Deferred Readback - Name Alone Does Not Trigger Readback",
  "description": "User provides only their name. Because guest_name is an input to BookReservation (which has readback_inputs: True), it goes to deferred — the framework does NOT read it back immediately. Instead it proceeds to ask for special_requests. Once both are collected, a single combined readback fires for both. Verifies that a partial group does not block collection or trigger premature confirm/reject.",
  "tags": [
    "slot-machine",
    "readback",
    "deferred-readback",
    "group-readback",
    "critical"
  ],
